Aim. To design and analyze a threat model for web application by identifying surface.

Theery: 
       Threat Modeling it is a systematic process used to identify, evaluating and mitigate security risks in a system, it helps developers understand how attackers con expléit vulnerability.
       can exploits the vulnerabilities.

STRIDE Model:

Stride is a most widely used threat modeling fromework developed by microsoft

Spoofing: impersonating user

Tampering: Modification of data.

Reputation Denying action without tracebility

Information: leakage of sensitive data. dotale service? Making system vulnerable. Denial-of-service

Elevation of priviledge: Making system vulnerable.

Methodology:

1) Identify Components

User, Login Page

Database

2) Identify Attack surface.

legin form inputs

Authentication system

Data transmission between client and server.

3) STRIDE Analysis.

STRIDE Cotegery                      Threat Example                                           Impact

Spoofing                             Credential, stuffing, , stuffing, brute force            Unauthorized login

Tampering                             sql injection on login form                             Database compromise

Reputation                            No logging of login attempts                            No Traceability

Info Disclosure                       Plaintext Password storage                              Data leakage

Denial of service                     Repeated login attempts                                 Server overload

Priviledge Escalation                 Bypassing authentication                                Admin access


Project Idea:

Behaviour biometrics authentication

Whenever a user login, the system captures behavioural data such as:

1)Typing speed

2)Mouse Movement

